Sentencas: The article carried out the Sol-Gel Method to synthesize Ce1-xErxOy (x=0.00, 0.10, 0.15, 0.20, 0.25, 0.30) (EDC) powders, as the anode materials of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Preparation and Properties of Erbium-Doped Ceria (EDC) for IT-SOFC Anodes in Natural Gas

Sentencas: The NiO-EDC anode-supported cells were fabricated by dry-pressing process using Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta (GDC) as electrolyte and La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8FeO0.2O3-delta(LSCF)-Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta(GDC) as cathode.
Titulo: Preparation and Properties of Erbium-Doped Ceria (EDC) for IT-SOFC Anodes in Natural Gas

Sentencas: The crystal forms, microstructures and chemical stability were investigated by XRD and SEM.
Titulo: Preparation and Properties of Erbium-Doped Ceria (EDC) for IT-SOFC Anodes in Natural Gas

Sentencas: The performances of single cells were tested by using humidified natural gas (3% H2O) as fuel and oxygen as oxidant in the temperature range from 400 degrees C to 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and Properties of Erbium-Doped Ceria (EDC) for IT-SOFC Anodes in Natural Gas

Sentencas: The results show that the anode of the cell represents good open-framework; The 50% NiO-50% Ce0.85Er0.15O gamma(E15C85) anode-supported cell demonstrates the best electrochemical performance among the eleven cells composed of different anodes.
Titulo: Preparation and Properties of Erbium-Doped Ceria (EDC) for IT-SOFC Anodes in Natural Gas

Sentencas: The maximum current density and power density are 117.84 mA.cm(-2) and 24.37 mW.cm(-2) tested at 650 degrees C respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and Properties of Erbium-Doped Ceria (EDC) for IT-SOFC Anodes in Natural Gas
